reviewText: This movie could very well be placed in the comedy section, but not because of the witty dialog or the theme, but because this movie has some of the absolute worst acting ever burned into film. You have to chuckle at  the constant hesitation and inability to speak lines. The only redeeming  feature of this flick is its shameless showing of breasts; a breast makes  an appearance at least once ever 15 minutes.

I am sure this was never intended to be more than a B drive in movie which it succeeded at nicely, and yes the plot was never intended to be anymore than a fun bit of silliness. so given that the acting was probably as good as could be hoped for{ I thoroughly enjoyed it!} And considering the overall budget I think the special effects were pretty fair. And  after having sat through epic stink fests like the titanic,[yep thought it was crapola!]  {water world yeeesh!} or the postman to name but a few big budget films that made me glad that smella vision hasn't hit the market yet lol. Anyway if your looking for a  simple plot and TNA movie this one should serve you well! AND with amazon prime its free! Oh and I'm sorry if I offended any ones delicate sensibilities how ever if you have  those why did you watch this movie in the first place? lol.
Lots of fun with good acting a great cast and out of this world special effects and non stop action!

This movie is incredible. Anyone who says otherwise has no sense of fun. The dialogue, the sound effects (A SLIDE WHISTLE! HONESTLY!) and the 50 cent dinosaurs knock it out of the park. Anyone who can watch the "OH, RIGHT IN THE KISSER!" scene without convulsing in laughter needs their head checked.

And yes, I've never seen so many bare breasts in anything outside of a Russ Meyer film. It's like, how they say hello. Absolutely unreal, which somehow makes it even more hilarious.

Would recommend to any true B-movie fan. Unless you're a kid using your mom's amazon account. Go study.

Not really, but they simulate Playboy Bunnies.  This movie must have gotten its high rating from all the male viewers since it is mainly scantily clad females with the occasional female on female bathing scene and TONS of "booby" scenes.  The acting is mediocre, at best; the dinosaurs are awful, sort of a cross between Claymation and puppetry - but worse.  The plot is thin, barely there - comedy is worth a few chuckles with some poorly timed one liners and corny as all get out.  But guys, you want some nice "booby" shots from pretty women?  Then this movie is for you!

I find it hard to believe that this truly, purposely funny ( very campy  ) movie is not available on DVD! It really does have some of the worst special effects ever, but who really cares about bad effects and lousy, cheap dinosaurs, when it offers some of the truly best B movie actresses ever! It's a classic DD, err I mean B, soft porn flick!! I'm a great fan of Michelle Bauer and go to great lengths to find her films!. Griffin Drew is way above average in every way, Nikki Fritz is always a presence,and Toni Naples , Becky Lebeau , and Antonia  Dorian truly roouunnndd out the fine Cast. If You like cute well rounded women running around half-naked for an hour and a half, ( This is what I bought it for and why love it! ) than you won't be disappointed. If you buy it thinking of Oscar movies, then save The Money to buy Dr. Zhivago. I love B and DD movies and this is one of my favorites. Net Flix carries a High Def copy of this for streaming. I wish they would make this this into a DVD !  They have high def copies of a lot of other crummy movies that I,d give anything to have on DVD.Bummer!!!

Group of misfit soldiers crash on an island with gorgeous, scantily clad women, and also inhabited by dinosaurs. The girls are good looking and tend to shed their clothes at the drop of the hat. The dinosaurs are rubber toys that look cheap. The acting and dialogue is terrible, but if you are looking for a simple movie with a good bit of nudity (mostly topless) then this movie is for you.
Hilarious and very tongue in cheek. Cute storyline and just the right amount of skin for light adult entertainment. Hubby and I loved it.

Movie was not worth the time to sit through . Poorly trained actors ,special effects was to laugh at. the battle scenes was like watching kids preform. Lots of boobs & attractive women is about the only redeeming thing about it (Me being a dirty old man) . The whole movie was a real bad waste of time. DINOSAUR ISLAND is a Jim wynorski / Fred Olen Ray film. As such, it contains an island full of beautiful, boulder-breasted women, and a few dinosaurs wandering around. Plot? A plane carrying a group of soldiers crashes on the island of the title. While ogling the uber-babes, a giant, horribly-animated reptile attacks! After the big lizard runs off, the soldiers are captured by the island girls, who believe that one of them is their "savior", predicted by "the sacred scrolls". Then, it's off w/ the bikini tops and in for a swim! Next, it's into the stone-age hot tub! You get the idea. Toni Naples stars as Queen Morgana. Enjoy...

I viewed this because I LIKE Dinosaurs, monsters, etc. Ray Harryhausen it's not, but in it's own way, it's not that bad. I've seen TERRIBLE movies (In my opinion), that got better reviews than this one! (Attack of the Killer Tomatoes for instance. I would rate Tomatoes a -4 if it were possible!) This movie is WAY better! Amazonian Warrior Women, Mild Porn, (Bare Breasts), lots of comedy. Not the best F/X, but then again, not the worst, either. For example: The Dinosaur eating the wounded soldier; if a real Dinosaur ate in this fashion, it would most likely choke. (Somebody would have to perform the Heimlich Maneuver on it.) Overall, I found it amusing. (Not boring, not scary, not the best acting, but amusing. I'm going to look for the DVD to purchase.)
Poor acting, over done story line. Terrible cheap dinosaurs.  Would guess most watch it for simulated sex Most likely, no Dinosaur Island 2.

A very improbable story line leads to a fair bit of fun. Not the best acting you've ever seen but if you suspend your criticism of the story and the acting then the movie is enjoyable. The special effects are adequate, not spectacular. What is spectacular is the scantily clad women in numbers and attraction, some corny stuff in the dialogue but worth a look and a laugh.
This has everything you'd expect from great soft porn - a completely unbelievable plot, cliches galore, wooden acting, and casting based on breast size.

This movie is a man`s movie, this is a straight man`s movie and perhaps if you not a straight man you won`t detect the cinematic genius, and intellectual sutlety in this well intentioned Masterpiece with all of its many blessed acttresses. This is one of those movies where there truly is a happy ending that men with buy. I recommend this to any men who are bored and want to contact their good humours.

This is a very cheesy film featuring soft core movie stars. The dinosaurs are as realistic as sock puppets and they make Gumby look human. American soldiers are stranded on an island inhabited by what appears to be a casting call for an Andy Sidoris film. The women are extremely beautiful and don't grow leg or armpit hair. They do bath topless and frolic in the water like girls at the Playboy mansion. They don't tan very well either.

The bad news is that the guys must kill "The Great One" (not Jackie Gleason) a sock puppet version of T. Rex. Corney jokes and lines abound, nothing that is a knee slapper. Make no mistake, the nudity is the main attraction with a token cat fight.

Parental guide: No f-bombs, sex, nudity (Antonia Dorian, Michelle Bauer, Griffin Drew, Toni Naples, Nikki Fritz, Becky LeBeau)

Another low budget masterpiece.  What made this movie for me was the lead females, all very attractive, all very naked.  I first saw this as a young lad, and unable to find more graphic presentations of lovely women, I enjoyed this immensely.  There is some softcore sex though, so be warned.

The plot isn't bad, and the acting is surpringly good.  The dinosaurs are thoroughly unconvincing, but who cares?  In movies like these, you've got to play along or why bother watching?

It's not a great movie, but for what the cast and crew had to work with, it's a damn fine effort.  If you enjoy low budget cinema, I whole-heartedly recommend it.

Definitely NOT for children though.

I'm at a lost as to why this movie has yet to have had an official (And uncut) dvd release. I taped it off of Cinemax about 25 years ago and thought it was terrific, especially since it starred two of my favorite B-movie actors ever, Ross Hagen and Michelle Baur. When I see that most similar movies form the 90's have long ago been released on dvd, it makes me wonder what's keeping this one off dvd release lists?
